com.inrix.sdk

Class TileManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inrix.sdk.TileManager

  • public class TileManager
extends Object
    Manages asynchronous retrieval of traffic tiles, which are images that contain traffic information that can be combined with maps.

    Note: The getTrafficTileUrl methods do not make HTTP requests, which means that they will immediately return a URL that can be used to obtain the image (if possible). If the client is not authenticated yet, or authentication token is expired, all getTrafficTileUrl methods will return null until a new token is obtained.

      • getTileUrl

        public final String getTileUrl(int x,
                int y,
                int zoom)
        Creates a url to obtain a tile bitmap. All default tile options will be used. If it's necessary to configure tile options, use TileManager.getTileUrl(int, int, int, com.inrix.sdk.TileManager.TileOptions) that accepts TileOptions as parameter.
        Parameters:
        x - Traffic tile X coordinate.
        y - Traffic tile Y coordinate.
        zoom - Current zoom level.
        Returns:
        The url that can be used to obtain the tile.
        Throws:
        TileManager.TileManagerException - when one of the specified arguments is invalid.

      • getTileUrl

        public String getTileUrl(int x,
                int y,
                int zoom,
                TileManager.TileOptions options)
        Retrieves a URL to obtain a traffic tile bitmap using center position and zoom level.
        Parameters:
        x - Traffic tile X coordinate.
        y - Traffic tile Y coordinate.
        zoom - An integer between 0 and 21 where 0 is zoomed out to cover the full globe, and 21 is the maximum zoom level. Note that some zoom levels may be too high or too low for this method to return an image.
        options - The tile configuration options.
        Returns:
        The URL that can be used to obtain the traffic tile.
        Throws:
        TileManager.TileManagerException - when any of the specified arguments is invalid.

      • getTileUrl

        public final String getTileUrl(String quadKey,
                TileManager.TileOptions options)
        Retrieves a URL that can be used to obtain a traffic tile bitmap using a virtual earth quad key.
        Parameters:
        quadKey - A virtual earth quad key to generate a resulting 256 x 256 tile which represents the described area.
        options - The tile configuration options.
        Returns:
        The URL that can be used to obtain the traffic tile.
        Throws:
        TileManager.TileManagerException - when quadkey is invalid or options contains invalid parameters.
